ularies of the nuns of St.-Julien and of the cathedral chapter, the latter existing only in fragmentary form. With full annotation of people and places and English-language summaries, these cartularies make a valuable contribution to our understanding of this significant episcopal centre’s history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCartularies. 0aMonasticism and religious orders for womenzFrancezAuxerrexHistoryyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266228540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442662285423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442662285.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK